<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the polymorphic
    `x_[scope]_case_party` custom table inside the scoped application
    `x_[scope]`.

    This table is the centerpiece of the AAP's "Polymorphic association via
    single-table choice + UI Policy" pattern (AAP Section 0.4.3). It COLLAPSES
    TWO ArkCase JPA entities into a single ServiceNow scoped table:

      1. com.armedia.acm.plugins.person.model.PersonAssociation
         (acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
         com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonAssociation.java),
         JPA-mapped to the MySQL table `acm_person_assoc` and using
         `cm_class_name` as a single-table-inheritance discriminator with
         a @ManyToOne(optional=false) Person reference.

      2. com.armedia.acm.plugins.person.model.PersonOrganizationAssociation
         (acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-person-plugin/src/main/java/
         com/armedia/acm/plugins/person/model/PersonOrganizationAssociation.java),
         JPA-mapped to the MySQL table `acm_person_org_assoc` and using the
         same `cm_class_name` discriminator with @ManyToOne(optional=false)
         references to BOTH Person AND Organization.

    The collapse strategy:
      - Two MySQL tables -> one ServiceNow scoped table (x_[scope]_case_party).
      - The class-name discriminator (`cm_class_name`) is replaced by a
        `party_type` Choice field with values Person and Organization, defined
        in ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_party_type.xml and enumerated
        in ../choices/sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml.
      - The @ManyToOne Person reference is replaced by the `person` field
        (Reference -> sys_user), defined in
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_person.xml.
      - The @ManyToOne Organization reference is replaced by the `organization`
        field (Reference -> core_company), defined in
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_organization.xml.
      - The parentId / parentType / parentTitle fields collapse into a single
        `case` reference field (Reference -> x_[scope]_case), defined in
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_case.xml. Conceptually, the parent
        type is fixed to "case" in this POC.
      - The personType / personToOrganizationAssociationType strings collapse
        into a single `role_label` String(100) field, defined in
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_role_label.xml.
      - The conditional visibility of `person` (when party_type=Person) and
        `organization` (when party_type=Organization) is enforced by the UI
        Policy in ../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml.

    Out-of-scope ArkCase fields explicitly NOT replicated per AAP Section 0.3.2:
      - Audit fields (created/modified/creator/modifier) - the platform supplies
        sys_created_on, sys_created_by, sys_updated_on, sys_updated_by, sys_id
        automatically because this is a sys_db_object record.
      - notes (PersonAssociation.notes column)
      - tags @ElementCollection (PersonAssociation -> acm_person_assoc_tag)
      - description (PersonOrganizationAssociation.cm_description)
      - primaryContact / defaultOrganization booleans
      - personDescription, parentTitle (rendering hints used by the AngularJS UI)

    This file authors ONLY table-level metadata (name, labels, parent class,
    scope linkage, auto-numbering reference, and access flags). The 5 fields
    enumerated in the AAP (case, party_type, person, organization, role_label)
    are authored as sys_dictionary records in the sibling ../dictionary/
    folder. The platform automatically inherits the standard sys_* audit
    columns by virtue of this record being a sys_db_object.

    Constraints honored:
      - Scoped-namespace exclusivity: every cross-reference resolves into the
        x_[scope] scope; no global-scope writes.
      - Zero hardcoded sys_id literals in any reference field; sys_scope,
        sys_package, and number_ref all resolve by scope name via the `source`
        attribute. The sys_id element below is THIS record's own primary key
        (deterministic MD5 of the table name `x_[scope]_case_party`) and is
        not a reference to any other record.
      - super_class is empty: this table extends NOTHING. It does not extend
        the OOB `task` or `incident` tables (which would write to global scope
        and violate AAP Section 0.3.2). The fact that the ArkCase source
        entities used JPA single-table inheritance (InheritanceType.SINGLE_TABLE)
        does NOT mean the ServiceNow target should extend an OOB table - the
        polymorphism is implemented declaratively through the `party_type`
        Choice field, not through table inheritance. The platform still
        provides standard sys_* audit columns because sys_db_object records
        always do.
      - extension_model is empty: this is not an extended table; it is a
        free-standing user-data table.
      - is_extendable is false: this POC table is not designed to be
        sub-classed. The polymorphism is at the row level via party_type, not
        at the schema level via subclassing.
      - create_access_controls is false: ServiceNow auto-creates a default
        ACL set when this is true. Since ../acl/x_[scope]_case_party_*.xml
        enumerates a precise role x table x CRUD matrix that mirrors the
        case-table ACL pattern (case_manager full access; case_agent restricted
        to parties belonging to assigned cases; case_viewer read-only), the
        auto-generated ACLs would conflict and are explicitly suppressed here.
      - The reference targets sys_user (for `person`) and core_company (for
        `organization`) are OOB ServiceNow tables that this record does NOT
        modify. They are referenced ONLY via dictionary entries in
        ../dictionary/, never via super_class.
      - The literal [scope] placeholder is preserved throughout per AAP
        convention; the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine
        Studio creation time. At Update Set import time, the platform resolves
        every `source="x_[scope]"` reference against the
        scope's `name` field on sys_scope / sys_app rather than via sys_id,
        guaranteeing portability across PDIs.

    Cross-Update-Set load ordering (per AAP Section 0.5.2):
      - This record MUST be loaded AFTER ../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml and
        ../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml.
      - This record MUST be loaded AFTER
        ../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case_party.xml (referenced by
        number_ref).
      - This record MUST be loaded AFTER ../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml because
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_case.xml (loaded after this record)
        creates a Reference column whose target is x_[scope]_case.
      - This record MUST be loaded BEFORE all
        ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_party_*.xml records (they reference this
        table by `name`).
      - This record MUST be loaded BEFORE all
        ../acl/x_[scope]_case_party_*.xml records.
      - This record MUST be loaded BEFORE
        ../ui_policy/x_[scope]_case_party_conditional_fields.xml (the UI
        Policy references this table by `name`).
      - This record MUST be loaded BEFORE all
        ../seed-data/parties/x_[scope]_case_party_demo_*.xml records.
-->
<record_update table="sys_db_object">
